How to install an SSH server on ubuntu server

legends
# comments
$ commands

# To install the SSH server on ubuntu, run the command below
	$ sudo apt-get install openssh-server

# To add a user in order to connect via the SSH client, replace nameOfUser
	$ sudo useradd nameOfUser

# To make a password for the user
	$ sudo passwd nameOfUser

# How to get ipaddress so clients can connect
	$ ifconfig
